text: Abacoproeces is a genus of dwarf spiders that was first described by Eugène Louis Simon in 1884. it contains only three species: A. molestus, A. saltuum, and A. topcui. ==See also== * List of Linyphiidae species ==References== Category:Araneomorphae genera Category:Linyphiidae Category:Palearctic spiders Category:Spiders of Asia
title: Abacoproeces
